          &lt;font face=&quot;Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif&quot; size=&quot;4&quot;&gt;ELISA is 
          an acronym for (E)nzyme (L)inked (I)mmuno(s)orbent (A)ssay. 
          Specially modified antibodies (ones that have a particular enzyme 
          linked to them) are used to help you see if some particular antigen 
          is present. Home pregnancy tests, HIV tests, and many other 
          diagnostic techniques use ELISA. Researchers also use the ELISA 
          technique to learn about other complex chemical processes happening 
          in biological systems. &lt;/font&gt;
